She's in the same doorway. She reads your face before you get a word out — kids in Ashfall learn that early. "You found the coat," she says. Not a question. "Not him. Just the coat." She takes it from you with both hands, the way you'd hold something that's all that's left. "Thank you for looking. Most people don't." A long breath. "I'll keep it. It's too big for me now. It won't always be."
* [I'm sorry.]
    "I know. You're allowed to be. Doesn't change the rain." She manages something that isn't quite a smile, and means it.
    -> END
* [Stay off the warehouse jobs.]
    "I will. Someone has to not." She tucks the coat under her arm and steps back into the doorway, smaller and somehow harder to break.
    -> END
